quran[28]{c,v,t}:
  40,66,"Say, ‘I have been forbidden to worship those whom you invoke besides Allah, as manifest proofs have come to me from my Lord, and I have been commanded to submit to the Lord of all the worlds.’"
  40,67,"It is He who created you from dust, then from a drop of [seminal] fluid, then from a clinging mass, then He brings you forth as infants, then [He nurtures you] so that you may come of age, and then that you may become aged—though there are some of you who die earlier—and complete a specified term, and so that you may exercise your reason"
  40,68,"It is He who gives life and brings death. When He decides on a matter, He just says to it, ‘Be!’ and it is"
  40,69,"Have you not regarded those who dispute the signs of Allah, where they are being led away [from Allah’s way]"
  40,70,—Those who deny the Book and what we have sent with Our apostles. Soon they will know
  40,71,"when they are dragged [with] iron collars and chains around their necks"
  40,72,into scalding waters and then set aflame in the Fire
  40,73,"Then they will be told, ‘Where are they whom you used to worship as deities"
  40,74,"besides Allah?’ They will say, ‘They have forsaken us. No, we did not invoke anything before.’ That is how Allah leads the faithless astray"
  40,75,"‘That [punishment] is because you used to boast unduly on the earth and because you used to strut"
  40,76,"Enter the gates of hell, to remain in it [forever].’ Evil is the [final] abode of the arrogant"
  40,77,"So be patient! Allah’s promise is indeed true. Whether We show you a part of what We promise them, or take you away [before that], [in any case] they will be brought back to Us"
  40,78,"Certainly We have sent apostles before you. Of them are those We have recounted to you, and of them are those We have not recounted to you. An apostle may not bring any sign except by Allah’s permission. Hence, when Allah’s edict comes, judgment is made with justice, and it is thence that the falsifiers become losers"
  40,79,"It is Allah who created the cattle for you that you may ride some of them, and some of them you eat"
  40,80,"and there are [numerous] uses in them for you, and that over them you may satisfy any need that is in your breasts, and you are carried on them and on ships"
  40,81,He shows you His signs. So which of the signs of Allah do you deny
  40,82,"Have they not travelled over the land so that they may observe how was the fate of those who were before them? They were more numerous than them and were greater [than them] in power and with respect to the effects [they left] in the land. But what they used to earn did not avail them"
  40,83,"When their apostles brought them manifest proofs, they boasted about the knowledge they possessed, but they were besieged by what they used to deride"
  40,84,"Then, when they sighted Our punishment, they said, ‘We believe in Allah alone, and disavow what we used to take as His partners.’"
  40,85,"But their faith was of no benefit to them when they sighted Our punishment—Allah’s precedent, which has passed among His servants, and it is thence that the faithless will be losers"
  41,1,"Ha, Meem"
  41,2,"A [gradually] sent down [revelation] from the All-beneficent, the All-merciful"
  41,3,"[this is] a Book whose signs have been elaborated for a people who have knowledge, an Arabic Quran"
  41,4,"a bearer of good news and a warner. But most of them turn away [from it], [and] so they do not listen"
  41,5,"They say, ‘Our hearts are in veils [which shut them off] from what you invite us to, and there is a deafness in our ears, and there is a curtain between us and you. So act [as your faith requires]; we too are acting [according to our own].’"
  41,6,"Say, ‘I am just a human like you. It has been revealed to me that your God is the One God. So worship Him single-mindedly and plead to Him for forgiveness.’ And woe to the polytheists"
  41,7,—those who do not pay the zakat and disbelieve in the Hereafter
  41,8,"As for those who have faith and do righteous deeds, there will be an everlasting reward for them"